Package Controllers

Class CustomersController

  • java.lang.Object
    • Controllers.CustomersController
  • public class CustomersController
extends java.lang.Object
    Main customers view that contains navigation buttons to other important views, a list of customers to be viewed, and which can be selected by a user to by modified or deleted. Users can also navigate to add customers from here.

      • setCustomerEditingButtonEvents

        private void setCustomerEditingButtonEvents()
        Sets actions for customer add, edit, and delete buttons. Add/edit trigger navigation to their pages and delete asks for user confirmation before doing so ONLY if customer has no appointments left in database.

      • refreshCache

        private void refreshCache()
                   throws java.sql.SQLException
        Clears local cache then repopulates with data from database
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - in case data could not be retrieved or database connection couldn't be established

      • setCustomerTableListener

        private void setCustomerTableListener()
        Sets listener for customers table. Adds validation prefix to ensure edit/delete functions aren't executed with null selections and sets selected customer to pass down to edit and delete pages. Lambda used for better iteration through customers in list to perform needed actions in response to a selection.

      • setCustomerColumns

        private void setCustomerColumns()
        Sets columns in customers table to relevant data from Customer class
